            "coding": [
              {
                "system": "urn:virpat:fhir:doc-type",
                "code": "patient-description"
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "subject": {
          "reference": "urn:uuid:11111111-1111-4111-8111-111111111111"
        },
        "payload": [
          {
            "contentString": "{patientName} is a 52-year-old woman in Czechia who comes to clinic for follow-up after routine blood work showed hyperlipidaemia [SNOMED:E78.5]. She is well appearing and not in acute distress, but she admits to persistent worry about her long-term cardiovascular health and sometimes fears having a heart attack when she reads about cholesterol and blocked arteries [SNOMED:E78.5]. She has not had focal neurologic symptoms, chest pain, or exertional dyspnea today, and the visit is centered on reducing future vascular risk related to elevated blood lipids and possible atherosclerosis [SNOMED:E78.5].\n\n{patientName} works full time in an office-based administrative role and spends much of the day sitting. Outside work she enjoys cooking for her family, gardening on weekends, and taking short evening walks with a close friend. She lives with her partner and keeps in regular contact with her adult daughter. Her lifestyle has been busy and somewhat sedentary, and she says meals are often convenient rather than carefully planned.\n\nIn conversation, {patientName} is thoughtful and engaged, asking practical questions about food choices, exercise, and whether medication will be lifelong. She is especially motivated because she has seen vascular disease in relatives and understands that hyperlipidaemia can contribute to atherosclerosis and increase the risk of ischemic stroke [SNOMED:E78.5]. She wants a realistic plan she can maintain while continuing work and family responsibilities."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "fullUrl": "urn:uuid:c3e3f09d-c970-4455-975d-51f4491955be",
      "resource": {
        "resourceType": "Communication",
        "status": "completed",
        "text": {
          "status": "generated",
          "div": "<div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">patient-history</div>"
        },
        "category": [
          {
            "coding": [
              {
                "system": "urn:virpat:fhir:doc-type",
                "code": "patient-history"
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "subject": {
          "reference": "urn:uuid:11111111-1111-4111-8111-111111111111"
        },
        "payload": [
          {
            "contentString": "{patientName} reports no prior myocardial infarction, no prior ischemic stroke, and no known diagnosed atherosclerotic cardiovascular disease, though she understands hyperlipidaemia is associated with atherosclerosis and ischemic stroke risk [SNOMED:E78.5]. She was informed of elevated cholesterol on recent screening and is now seeking treatment [SNOMED:E78.5].\n\nShe has had no recent hospitalizations and no major prior surgeries. She has a mostly sedentary work routine, tries to walk a few times per week, and says her diet has included frequent rich meals and pastries. She does not report tobacco use, and alcohol intake is occasional by history. She describes intermittent health anxiety centered on the possibility of a future heart attack after learning about her cholesterol [SNOMED:E78.5]."
          }
        ]
      }
